{
  "step": 3,
  "title": "The Craving Trap",
  "startFrame": 3217,
  "endFrame": 4770,
  "componentPath": "src/visuals/Generated_TheCravingTrap.tsx",
  "transcriptSegment": "Every coding challenge now triggers an immediate craving to just ask the A I. You'll be staring at a perfectly solvable bug, and your brain starts generating excuses. \"It'll be faster this way.\" \"I can learn from the A I's approach.\" \"I'm being efficient with my time.\" But efficiency isn't the real driver here. The craving is.\n\nThe most insidious part is that knowing you're addicted doesn't help you stop. Addiction never works that way. In 2023, git hub surveyed developers who recognized their over-dependence on Copilot. Ninety-one percent said they wanted to reduce their usage. Only twelve percent actually managed to do it for more than a week. The knowledge that something is bad for you doesn't override the neurochemical compulsion to keep doing it.",
